Auntie Life took over. And we are thriving hunny.🍯🧡

Another day in the Life of Kai. Took him to the Mets game. He got to meet my friend Tommy Pham. He doesn’t fully understand it all now. But building these memories with him when he looks back and is older. He will have so many special moments to look back on and tell his friends. I want him to see what his future can be with passion and drive. And to only have him around people he can idolize to pursue larger than life dreams. I always want to instill hope in him. Yesterday was the perfect day. Thank you Pham for making it the perfect evening for Kai. 🧡💙

Tonight I met my childhood hero. And the little biracial girl I once was, was over the moon. I never had someone who looked like me growing up in the 90’s to idolize or who went through life’s adversities as I did. So to meet the woman and pay respect as to why I had such an influence as in “I can go out into the world and be someone.” Was because of her. I held back tears but everyone in the room could feel when we spoke to each other the child in us came out because for that moment we knew what this meant. I cried during her concert. And I’ll cry again remembering this moment. Thank you @mariahcarey 

And this is about the dumbest pic I’ve ever took and posted so you know how much I love her

There’s one thing that I’ve come to acknowledge in this life, and sit with the thought that life and time is fleeting from us all. And every possible moment you have to spare you find your way back home to whom ever that may be that loves you. For me I have to grab each moment I have to spare. Because I know my conscious will rest easy never saying “I wish” I spent more time with the ones I love. Whoever you have in that circle of love. Hold them tight and dearly. For it is truly a blessing not all are gifted to have. Never take these moments for granted. Shes dragging me to church on a Saturday. And you know what, it’s simply fine just surrendering to life and another moment I have to be with her. During the holidays no matter what it may look like for you. I challenge everyone to alter their frame of mind and see the beauty of what moments can be, despite your personal wants and dont’s, by embracing what’s in front of you. Happy holidays from mama and I.

Late on these new years post, but I think it’s not about a new year new you. Self evolution is constant just as the earth rotates. I am a million women in one contained body. What I’ve learned, over the year I’ve grown,  and over the years I’ve truly grown. But right here right now today and all my yesterdays I’ve challenged myself little by little to open my heart, even when it wants to close quickly. I try to practice to continue to pry it back open, that’s not easy, it’s a fight with my ego. Whether it be pain allowing myself to go through it because, that much faster you can allow the healing process. Or allowing myself to open my heart and surrender to vulnerability, to speaking words that may make others feel uncomfortable but it allows me to feel free from wonder. Surrendering to the thought that what I want, may not be for me but never stop trying. To try new things that allow me to grow, but also put me in the hot seat of un comfortability and inconvenience, but that my mind can open more to the thought of new things, I’ve turned my back on before. If I’m lucky I have another 60 years of growth and self evolution. But right here today. I’m grateful that over the years I’m still opening my heart for more to flow in. So if I must box this coming year into 2 words. For me it will be Self evolution. Grow to glow 🌱✨
